ðŸ›¡ï¸ 2. Defensive Techniques (Defender Perspective)

ðŸ” General Hardening

â€¢ Limit publicly available data (e.g., use privacy in Whois, limit metadata exposure).
â€¢ Split DNS to separate internal and public records.
â€¢ Restrict DNS zone transfers to authorized servers only.
â€¢ Harden SSL/TLS: Use subdomain monitoring via Certificate Transparency alerts.

âš™ï¸ OWA/Exchange Hardening

â€¢ Block NTLM where possible or limit endpoint exposure.
â€¢ Monitor for login anomalies (rate-limiting, thresholds).
â€¢ Track timing discrepancies in login behavior.

ðŸ›‘ Recon-Awareness

â€¢ Regularly self-scan with Shodan, Censys, crt.sh to see whatâ€™s publicly exposed.
â€¢ Monitor Wayback Machine entries and remove outdated/obsolete content.
â€¢ Maintain alert lists for lookalike domains or exposed certificates.



